Effect of Genetic Variants on DEG with comparison to Satterstrom

1. Abstract

Single-cell genomics identifies cell typespecific molecular changes in autism data4,5 cell type satterstrom gene list overlap ASD DEG , DEG pLI score Effect of Genetic Variants on ASD Risk .

Satterstrom gene list DEG ASD risk . Satterstrom 2020 cohort sample study sample size , . rare and de novovariants defining , pLI score MPC(missensebadness, PolyPhen-2, constraint) score Transmission and De Novo Association Test (TADA), ASDP, ASDNDD and DDD gene heterogeneity analyses, Genes in Recurrent Genomic Disorders (GD) 102 ASD . satterstrom gene list (102 ASD) .

ASD DEG fold change cell type , sattterstrom gene data4 DEG satterstorm gene gene . satterstrom gene association with ASD . gene pLI Large-Scale Exome Sequencing Study Implicates Both Developmental and Functional Changes in the Neurobiology of Autism supplemental data table 2 . gene gene with high reliablity, HR_gene .

pLI probability of loss-of-function intolerance LOF variants . pLI LOF ASD risk , 0.95 .

raw data (excel file) packages .

library(tidyverse)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(readxl)
library(ggrepel)
library(ggthemes)

Attaching package: ggthemes

The following object is masked from package:cowplot:

    theme_map
library(cowplot)
data4 <- readxl::read_xls("aav8130_Data-S4.xls")

head(data4)

Cell type, Gene name, Fold change, q value, Satterstrom tidy format .

d4 <- data4 %>% select(`Cell type`, `Gene name`, `Fold change`, `q value`, Satterstrom)

Cell type cell line , ASD hetero geneous neurodevelopmental condition cell line neuron .

neuron = c("L2/3","L4","L5/6","L5/6-CC","Neu-mat","Neu-NRGN-I","Neu-NRGN-II","IN-PV","IN-SST","IN-VIP","IN-SV2C" )
d4 <- d4 %>% mutate(neuronal = ifelse(`Cell type` %in% neuron, "neuron", "non-neuron"))
d4_n <- d4 %>% filter(neuronal=="neuron")
d4_nn <- d4 %>% filter(neuronal=="non-neuron")
head(d4)

HR_gene d4 data pLI Large-Scale Exome Sequencing Study Implicates Both Developmental and Functional Changes in the Neurobiology of Autism supplemental data table 2 merge.

d4_s = d4 %>% filter(Satterstrom=="yes") %>% rename('gene' = `Gene name`)
d4_s_gn = d4_s$gene
d4_sat = satterstrom_102ASD %>% filter(gene %in% d4_s_gn)
d4_s_sat = merge(d4_s, d4_sat, by = 'gene')

3. Visualization

d4 visualization Cell type DEG fold change neuron, Satterstrom gene volcano plot .

3.1 1st Plot - DEG Fold Change by Cell type (feat.Satterstrom)


p1<- d4_n %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=`Fold change`, y= -log10(`q value`), col= `Cell type`)) + 
  geom_point(size=1.0, alpha=0.8) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.0, color="gray", size= 1.5) +
  geom_label_repel(data=d4_n %>% filter(Satterstrom=="yes"),aes(label=`Gene name`),size=3.5, nudge_x = 0.2, nudge_y = 0.1)+
  ggtitle("Neuron (n=458)")+
  xlim(c(1.0,-1.0))+
  ylab("-log10(q value)")+
  theme_tufte()+
  theme(axis.line = element_line(size = 1,colour = "black"))+
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        legend.background = element_rect(fill="lightblue",
                                  size=0.5, linetype="solid", 
                                  colour ="darkblue"),
        legend.key.size = unit(3,'mm'),
        plot.title = element_text(size=20, face = "bold"),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 15))+
  guides(color=guide_legend(nrow = 2))

p2<- d4_nn %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=`Fold change`, y= -log10(`q value`), col= `Cell type`)) + 
  geom_point(size=1.0, alpha=0.8)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.0, color="gray", size= 1.5) + 
  geom_label_repel(data=d4_nn %>% filter(Satterstrom=="yes"),aes(label=`Gene name`),size=3.5, nudge_x = 0.2, nudge_y = 0.1)+
  ggtitle("NonNeuron (n= 234)")+
  xlim(c(1.0,-1.0))+
  ylab("-log10(q value)")+
  theme_tufte()+
  theme(axis.line = element_line(size = 1,colour = "black"))+
  theme(legend.position ="bottom",
        legend.background = element_rect(fill="lightblue",
                                  size=0.5, linetype="solid", 
                                  colour ="darkblue"),
        legend.key.size = unit(3,'mm'),
        plot.title = element_text(size=20, face = "bold"),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 15))+
  guides(color=guide_legend(nrow = 2))

plot_row <- plot_grid(p1,p2)



title <- ggdraw() +
  draw_label(
    "DEG Fold Change by Cell type (feat.Satterstrom) ",
    fontfamily = "serif",
    fontface = 'bold',
    color = '#0C1783',
    x = 0,
    hjust = 0,
    size = 20
  ) 
plot1 <-plot_grid(
  title, plot_row,
   ncol = 1,
  rel_heights = c(0.1, 1)
)

3.2 2nd Plot - pLI of HR_gene

volcaono plot label HR_gene pLI heatmap visualization.

rd <- d4_s_sat %>% select(`Cell type`, gene, pLI)
rd <- rd %>% pivot_wider(names_from = gene, values_from = pLI) 
rd <- pivot_longer(rd,!`Cell type`, names_to = 'gene', values_to = 'pLI')

plot2 <- ggplot(rd, aes(x=gene, y=`Cell type`, fill=pLI)) + 
  geom_tile(color="black")+
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, vjust = 0.8, hjust = 1))+
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Spectral", na.value = "ivory")+
  ggtitle('pLI of HR_gene')+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(family = "serif", face = "bold", size = 20))
